{"decision":"search","userMessageId":61014208,"agentMessageId":75707961,"answer":"Hugging Face Inc. is a French-American company headquartered in New York City, specializing in developing computational tools for building applications utilizing machine learning. Initially founded in 2016 by French entrepreneurs Clément Delangue, Julien Chaumond, and Thomas Wolf in New York City, the company pivoted from developing a chatbot app targeted at teenagers to focusing on being a platform for machine learning. The company is widely recognized for its Transformers library, which is designed for natural language processing applications and includes open-source implementations of transformer models for text, image, and audio tasks. This library, compatible with deep learning frameworks like PyTorch, TensorFlow, and JAX, encompasses implementations of prominent models such as BERT and GPT-2. Apart from the Transformers library, Hugging Face has developed the Hugging Face Hub, a platform for hosting Git-based code repositories, models, datasets, and web applications specifically for small-scale demonstrations of machine learning applications. Furthermore, Hugging Face offers additional libraries including \"Datasets\" for dataset processing, \"Evaluate\" for model evaluation, and \"Gradio\" for machine learning demos.\n\nHugging Face also provides a collaborative environment that enables data scientists, researchers, and machine learning engineers to share ideas, seek support, and contribute to open-source projects. The company has established strong collaborations, highlighted by its partnership with Amazon Web Services (AWS) to make Hugging Face's products available to AWS customers as building blocks for their custom applications. Hugging Face has received significant funding and investment from well-established organizations such as Google, Amazon, Nvidia, Salesforce, and others. These investments have notably","modelType":"","references":[{"title":"Hugging Face - Wikipedia",